  "prompt": "What are some funniest Indian English phrases that people use?",
  "response": "Here are some hilarious Indian English phrases and their humorous meanings:\n\n1. \"What is your good name?\"\n- A formal way of asking someone's name\n\n2. \"Prepone\" (opposite of postpone)\n- To schedule something earlier than originally planned\n\n3. \"Do one thing...\"\n- Used before giving advice or suggesting something\n\n4. \"Timepass\"\n- Killing time or doing something unproductive\n\n5. \"Mugging up\"\n- Memorizing something by heart\n\n6. \"Tight slap\"\n- A hard, embarrassing slap\n\n7. \"Timepass friendship\"\n- A casual, non-serious friendship\n\n8. \"Revert back\"\n- To reply or respond (redundant usage)\n\n9. \"Cent percent\"\n- 100% or completely\n\n10. \"Totally timepass movie\"\n- A movie with no serious plot or meaning\n\n11. \"Quite like that only\"\n- Agreeing with something without much enthusiasm\n\n12. \"Timepass chatting\"\n- Casual, meaningless conversation\n\nThese phrases are uniquely Indian and often sound hilarious to non-Indians. They reflect the creativity and humor in Indian English usage.",
